@lporiginalg - I encoded to disc using convertX and i'm watching it as i type.... i'm 10 minutes in and the sync is either perfect, or so slightly out-of-sync as to be imperceptible. I'm a real dick about sync problems - very picky - and i'm detecting no problem at all. Might change, but "from the very start" is bs, at least.

I'm getting a fairly regular glitchy noise (like a brief electronic squelch sound) every 30 seconds or so, but that might just be the burn. I have another copy burning now and will check it to see if the sound repeats (and anyone queuing up to make 'people still burn?' comments... yeah, they do, because they like to share with people who only have dvd players) 

 -- just checked the 2nd copy...same problem. Could just be my encode (doubt it, but could be). If people are making archive copies for themselves though, i'd check it first to make sure it's up to your own standards.
